The paper proposes a method for automatically assessing the quality of image registration in clinical FLAIR MRI scans of the brain using deep learning-based ventricle segmentation. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as segmentation and registration, which are commonly found in the cs.CV sub-category. The use of neural networks for segmentation also suggests the possibility of machine learning (ML) techniques, which are commonly found in the cs.LG and cs.NE sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of an atlas for registration, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (AI) and medical imaging. Finally, the paper discusses the potential clinical applications of the proposed method, which could fall under the cs.MM sub-category.
